Governor of Imo State, Hope Uzodinma, has announced the appointment of Barr Nnamdi Anyaehie as Chief of Staff; Chief Oguike Nwachukwu as Chief Press Secretary/Media Adviser; Chief Cosmas Iwu as Secretary to the State Government (SSG) and C.O.C Akaolisa as Attorney-General. The appointments, according to the governor, take immediate effect. Uzodinma was declared the winner of March 9, 2019 governorship election by the Supreme Court Imo: Okorocha, APC exco absent as Uzodinma launches guber campaign Uzodinma wants to be gov to evade prosecution - Okorocha JUST IN: INEC issues Certificate of Return to Imo governor, Uzodinma